        <updateDate>2020-12-01T16:16:06Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Pell Grant Restoration Act</b> <b>of 2019</b></p> <p> This bill restores a student's Pell Grant eligibility for any period of time during which the student qualified for, or would have qualified for, federal student loan forgiveness due to school closure, assertion of a defense against repayment, or institutional fraud or misconduct. </p> <p>Specifically, this bill provides that Pell Grants received by a student during that period of time do not count toward the student's lifetime Pell Grant eligibility period (currently 12 full-time semesters). </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
